Create Tables and associate with Main Data table 10

Step 1- Create a Calendar table and create relationship





1-  Click on Modeling Ribbon

2-  Select new table.

3-  Erase Table and add the syntax to create the new table based on the dates that include all calendar in the data.

           Date Dim = CALENDAR (1/1/1996, 12/31/2021)

4- Click the Data view on the left and see the Date information. 

5-  Click on the Model view and create relationship between the tables by Dragging and drop to the related columns. 

         Step 2 - Create a Key Measure Table to populate with measures.


1- From Home ribbon, select Enter Data and name it, Key Measure.

2- Click Load

3- Right click on the newly created Key Measure table and select new measure.

4-  Erase the Measure and write your DAX measure.

5-  Enter.
